Package: portvine
Title: Portfolio level (un)conditional risk measure estimation for backtesting using vine copula and ARMA-GARCH models
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person('Emanuel', 'Sommer', email = 'emanuel_sommer@gmx.de',
    role = c('cre', 'aut'))
Description: Portfolio level risk estimates (like the Value at Risk or the Expected Shortfall) are estimated by modeling each asset univariately by an ARMA-GARCH model and then their dependence via a vine copula model in a rolling window fashion. One can even condition on variables/time series at certain quantile levels to stresstest the risk estimates.
